    "detail": "The location of the hotel is its best selling point. Couldn't be more convenient for those travelling to Narita airport by skyliner. The room itself is a little bit bigger than other Tokyo hotel rooms and for 1 person feels the right size. The bed is super soft which i thought it would be a problem but i have a suspicion that it is a memory mattress. Same with the pillows they are flat but again for me it wasn't a problem, as i got used to it within an hour. The TV screen is big with some Japanese channels and BBC world news that you can watch for free. Moneywise it was a bit expensive but again you are paying for the convenient location.",
